listing_jobDesc:
Collect, clean, store and analyse considerable amounts of heterogeneous data; 
Design and build out data science pipelines and models in production; 
Design and maintain the right setup for data visibility and actionability across the company; 
Work with the product teams on modelling and solving core problems like pricing, allocation and lead generation; 
Collaborate with the operations team on modelling key aspects of company growth; 
Always thrive, create a data informed culture where each individual can use data to make better decisions while being self-sufficient on getting that data; and 
Growth your own horizontal data team when the time arrives. 
Track record of performing data analysis over large amounts of heterogeneous data; 
Experience using statistics and machine learning to solve complex product and operation challenges; 
Experience with scripting technologies; 
Experience with data visualization tools such as Metabase, Tableau or similar; 
You are comfortable working in a discovery phase environment where most of the things are yet to be built; 
You are a good communicator when it comes to explaining data and your work. You’ll get to be part of building one of the fastest growing tech companies in culture, backed by early investors in companies like Skype, Farfetch, Glossier & Facebook

 We offer competitive salary, equity & holiday allowance, as well as flexible working hours

 We have offices in both London and Amsterdam and are fully supportive of remote working 
We have a learning & development budget for every person at the company

